EMExample#delayed should execute block in the instance of EMExample instead of instance of ExampleGroup

Huge specs refactoring: moved most interesting specs into adapter seg for unified adapter testing.

Note: I've butchered a lot of examples that seemed redundant.
But if we start seeing regressions, it will be so much easier to test new behavior
on all the adapters.
#delayed feature for examples

Removing connection error requirement from specs altogether.

It's kinda thing we can't control. On JRuby / Ubuntu Hardy the spec just hangs
and exits by timeout, which seems like a good enough resolution for me. I don't
see any harm if we await any error, not necessarily ConnectionError.

This is open to discussion, of course.
